3.JS--defines the behaviour of a webpage

**JS is a high level interpreted language used to make web pages interactive or dynamic
--->it runs directly in your browser
--->JS does the following
1.user interactivity--ability of the webpage to respond to user action e.g. button clicks,animations,form inputs
2.Reactivity

Writing JS
1.Internal JS--a script in a HTML file
   (i) script in the body section- right above the closing body tag(the recomended way)
   (ii) a script in the head section
2.External JS-----The best way
------create an external JS file with a .js extension and then limk to a html file using a source(src) attribute   

**VARIABLES**
A variable is a named container or memory space used to store values
--->ways of declaring variables in JS
1. using the let keyword
---most common way of declaring avariable
---variables declared using let can be re assigned meaning values can be changed
eg--- let x = 5// declaration
x = 10 reassigned//
2. using const keyword
---variables once declared cant be reasigned or changed in value
eg const name = "jane"--> this cant be changed
3. using the var keyword
---works just like let but its outdated it works in older browsers

JS DATATYPES
1.string-- represents textual data or charachters enclosed in quotation marks
2.Number--numeric values-- both whole numbers and decimal numbers
3.boolean--represents truth values -- true and false


How to output in JS...
console.log()
checking type of data = typeof()

**STRING METHODS & OPERATIONS**

- Methods are inbuilt functions used to manipulate data

1. Concatenation â€“ joining or combining strings
    a) Using "+" operator
    b) using concat() method
2. Template literals - a way of embedding or including variables inside strings
     -we use: backticks,dollar signs and curly braces   
3. Accessing charachters in a string- strings are ordered--use indexing
      n/b:-in accessing string charachters in JS, we dont have negative indexes 
4.determining no of charachters in a string-- we use .length   
5. .slice() returns a portion/ substring of a full string syntax=console.log(text.slice(0,4))
--slicing accepts negative index but it picks and moves forward not backwards
6. .toUppercase()--converts a string to uppercase format
7. .toLowercase()---converts a string to lowercase format
8. .includes()--checks whether a string has a specified charachters or substring--- and it returns a boolean
9. .startsWith()--checks whether a string starts with a specific char or substring they return boolean together with ends with
10. .endsWith() checks whether a string ends with a specific char or substring
11. .indexOf()---returns the first occurence of a specified charachter
12. .replace()---replaces specified charachter/s with an ew one
13. .trim()--removes all wide spaces around values  

